      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "you all. . . .",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The two clauses of the verse are distinct from each other. St. Paul’s first reason for sending Epaphroditus was in itself a sufficient one, that in his convalescence he yearned for home, and needed a change thither. The original is strong, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "because he was continually longing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Philippians 1:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Philippians 4:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for you all.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " But besides this he was “full of heaviness,” or more properly, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "distressed and uneasy, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because of the effect which the news of his apparently fatal illness might cause at home.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
