  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "26. For—reason for thinking it \"necessary to send\" \"Epaphroditus. Translate as Greek, \"Inasmuch as he was longing after you all.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "full of heaviness—The Greek expresses the being worn out and overpowered with heavy grief.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because that ye had heard that he had been sick—rather, \"that he was sick.\" He felt how exceedingly saddened you would be in hearing it; and he now is hastening to relieve your minds of the anxiety.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
