  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 26.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "For he longed after you all",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The verb is strengthened by the preposition: \"was eagerly longing.\" Perhaps it should be rendered. he \"is longing;\" like \"I count it necessary,\" in Ver. 25. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And was full of heaviness, because that ye had heard that he had been sick.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"Full of heaviness\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀδημονῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is the word used of our blessed Lord in his agony (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Some derive it from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἄδημος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", he away from home; others, more probably, from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἄδην",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in the sense of loathing, weariness, satiety. The word implies heart-sickness, restless; unsatisfied weariness, produced by some overwhelming distress. Philippians 2:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
